# App Hub Publisher — Project Rules

This repo is a **publisher kit** for **App Hub** (desktop host + app store). It does not ship sample apps. Publishers (or AI agents) create apps under `apps/<slug>/`. See `AGENTS.md` and `README.md` at repo root.

## Publisher URLs — local config only (required reading)

**All Hub URLs live in `apphub.publisher.json` at repo root.** That file is **gitignored** — each publisher copies from `apphub.publisher.example.json` and fills in their own values. **Never put real URLs in tracked files** (README, rules, or commits).

| Key | Purpose |
|-----|---------|
| `integration_docs_url` | Machine-readable integration contract (JSON) from your App Hub operator |
| `hub_portal_url` | Your App Hub portal (install, launch, store, upload) |

Setup after clone:

```bash
cp apphub.publisher.example.json apphub.publisher.json
# Edit apphub.publisher.json with your URLs (do not commit this file)
```

**App Hub** may inject URLs into this file when the publisher connects their instance.

### Agent behavior

1. **Read `apphub.publisher.json` first** (create from `apphub.publisher.example.json` if missing).
2. If `integration_docs_url` is **empty or missing**, **stop and ask the user** for their integration docs URL. Do not invent API hosts or paths.
3. If `hub_portal_url` is **empty or missing**, ask the user for their App Hub portal URL when deploy, testing, or store steps are needed.
4. When set, fetch `integration_docs_url` and treat it as the authoritative contract (`schema_version`, routes, bridge). HTTP paths in this rule file are **examples** — use `http.base_path` from the fetched docs.

**Official contract:** value of `integration_docs_url` in `apphub.publisher.json` only (not hardcoded in this repo).

## Language — English only (authoring)

All **source code**, **documentation**, **comments**, **commit messages**, **Cursor rules**, and **README files** in this repo must be written in **English**.

- Identifiers, function names, types, API payloads, logs, and error messages in code: **English**
- Inline comments and JSDoc/TSDoc: **English**
- User-facing UI copy: still localized via i18n (`en` + `vi` locale files) — see below

Do not add Vietnamese (or other language) prose in code, docs, or rules. Vietnamese strings belong only in `locales/vi.json` (and English in `locales/en.json`).

## Monorepo layout

- One app = **one folder** at repo root: `apps/<slug>/`
- Each app **builds, deploys, and runs independently** (own `package.json`, `manifest.json`, optional backend)
- No cross-imports between apps; share via `packages/` only when necessary (e.g. `packages/apphub-bridge/`)

```
apps/<slug>/
  PLAN.md          # living plan + per-step checklists (required)
  src/
    components/
    modules/       # api, stores, composables
    locales/       # en.json, vi.json
    themes/
  manifest.json    # runtime_type, permissions, api_urls
  package.json
  README.md
```

## Root `.gitignore` — applies to all apps

Maintain **one** `.gitignore` at the **repo root**. Do not duplicate per app unless an app has an exceptional local-only artifact — then add a one-line pointer in the app README, not a second full ignore file.

**Must be ignored (root patterns):**

| Category | Patterns |
|----------|----------|
| Dependencies | `node_modules/`, `.pnp`, `.pnp.js` |
| Build output | `dist/`, `build/`, `out/`, `.output/`, `.nuxt/`, `.next/`, `.vite/`, `*.tsbuildinfo` |
| Deploy bundles | `*.zip` (hosted Hub zips; exception only for intentional docs assets) |
| Secrets | `.env`, `.env.*` (allow `!.env.example`), `*.pem`, `*.key`, `secrets/`, launch-token files |
| Logs | `logs/`, `*.log`, `*-debug.log*` |
| Test/coverage | `coverage/`, `.nyc_output/`, `playwright-report/`, `test-results/` |
| Caches | `.cache/`, `.turbo/`, `.parcel-cache/`, `.eslintcache`, `.stylelintcache` |
| OS/editor junk | `.DS_Store`, `Thumbs.db`, `.idea/`, swap files — **do not** ignore `.cursor/rules/` |
| Hosting metadata | `.vercel/`, `.netlify/` |

Never commit: `.env`, tokens, `launch_token`, private keys, or generated `dist/` / deploy zips.

When adding a new tool stack (e.g. Python, Rust), extend **root** `.gitignore` once so every app inherits it.

## Per-app plan and checklists — required

Before starting work on an app (new or existing), create or open `apps/<slug>/PLAN.md`.

### PLAN.md structure

```markdown
# <App name> — Plan

## Goal
One paragraph: what this app does and success criteria.

## Phases

### Phase 1 — <name>
**Status:** not started | in progress | done

- [ ] Step 1.1 — ...
- [ ] Step 1.2 — ...

### Phase 2 — <name>
...
```

### Rules for plans and checklists

1. **Plan before doing** — outline phases and steps in `PLAN.md` before implementation (scaffold, feature, fix, or publish).
2. **Checklist per step** — every phase has concrete `- [ ]` items; one item = one verifiable outcome.
3. **Update on every change** — when you start, edit, finish, or drop work:
   - Mark items `[x]` when done
   - Add new steps if scope grows
   - Set phase **Status** (`not started` → `in progress` → `done`)
   - Add a short **Changelog** section at the bottom with date + what changed (optional but recommended)
4. **Keep in sync** — if code or manifest changes without updating `PLAN.md`, update the plan in the same session before considering the task complete.
5. **English only** — same language rule as code and docs.

Agents and contributors must read `PLAN.md` at the start of work on an app and update it before finishing.

## Runtime type — pick the right one

| | `hosted` | `iframe` |
|---|----------|----------|
| Host | Zip on Hub → `…/apps/{slug}/runtime/` | Publisher hosts SPA at `entry_url` (HTTPS) |
| Storage | `localStorage` shim — **await `window.__APPHUB_STORAGE__?.ready`** before first read | Normal `localStorage`/`sessionStorage` on publisher origin |
| Use when | Small tools, demos, no publisher HTTPS host | Full SPAs, auth, domain you control |

**Required manifest fields:** `runtime_type`, `permissions[]`, `api_urls[]` (if backend exists).  
For iframe, also: `entry_url`, optional `healthcheck_url`.

## Hosted runtime — zip layout and troubleshooting

Follow `audiences.publisher.hosted_runtime_troubleshooting` in the integration docs (schema `1.11.1+`). Summary for agents:

### Zip contract (hosted register)

- `manifest.json` **inside** the zip (at root or shallowest folder).
- Entry file: `manifest.main` / `index.html` must exist in the zip.
- Zip **build output only** (e.g. `dist/` contents) — never `node_modules`, `.cmd`, `.ps1`, or dev tooling.
- Typical layout at zip root: `manifest.json`, `index.html`, `assets/*.js`, `assets/*.css`.
- Max bundle size per integration docs (commonly ~50 MB).

### JavaScript / ES modules

- **ES modules are supported** (`<script type="module">`). Hashed names like `index-BmAhrHFo.js` come from **your bundler** (Vite), not a Hub-injected loader.
- Hub **does not** remove `type="module"`. It rewrites `src`/`href` to append `launch_token`, injects the storage shim, and serves `.js` as `application/javascript`.
- **`Cannot use import statement outside a module`** usually means a chunk returned **401, 404, or HTML** (browser runs error body as classic script), or `index.html` lost `type="module"`. Check DevTools Network: all `.js` → 200. **Not** a CSP `frame-ancestors` issue.

### CSP `frame-ancestors 'self'`

- Nested chain: product shell → Hub iframe → hosted runtime on API origin.
- **Publishers cannot fix this in the zip.** Platform team must allow Hub and product origins (`APPHUB_ALLOWED_HUB_ORIGINS`, `APPHUB_ALLOWED_PRODUCT_ORIGINS`). Report framing errors with your Hub and product URLs.

### Build tools (hosted)

- **Vite 5/6** with `type="module"` and `base: './'` is the recommended path. Zip `dist/` + `manifest.json` at zip root.
- IIFE builds are optional for debugging wiring only — not required for production.

## Bridge — required integration

### Connection flow

1. User opens app → Hub calls `POST /apps/{slug}/launch` → `entry_url` + `launch_token` + `scopes_granted`
2. App loads in a Hub window
3. Listen for **`apphub:bridge:ready`** (or use `window.AppHubBridge`)
4. UI uses `display_user`; **server auth** uses `GET bridge/user` from publisher backend

### postMessage protocol (channel: `apphub:bridge`)

| Direction | Event | Purpose |
|-----------|-------|---------|
| Parent → child | `apphub:bridge:ready` | Sends `context` (app_slug, launch_token, scopes_granted, display_user, …) |
| Child → parent | `apphub:bridge:call` | `{ id, method, args }` |
| Parent → child | `apphub:bridge:result` | `{ id, ok, result?, error? }` |

**Bridge methods:** `requestPermission`, `sendDesktopMessage`, `setTaskbarBadge`, `reportError`  
Copy/load `docs/sdk-stub.js` into your bundle or use `window.AppHubBridge`.

### Permissions

| Scope | Notes |
|-------|-------|
| `user.read` | User id + display name — granted at install |
| `user.profile` | Avatar, locale, etc. — granted at install |
| `desktop.notify` | For `POST bridge/notify` from **publisher backend** only |
| `desktop.message` | Request via `requestPermission` during session |
| `desktop.badge` | Request via `requestPermission` during session |

### Two user data tiers — do not mix them up

- **display_only** (`getDisplayUser()`, `display_user` on ready): greetings, UI labels — **not for auth**
- **authoritative** (`GET bridge/user` or `POST verify-launch-token` on publisher server): authorization, audit, server-side API

### launch_token — security

- Short-lived secret; treat like a password
- **Never** log, show in UI, or send to third parties
- Publisher backend passes token to `GET bridge/user` (headers `X-AppHub-Launch-Token`, `X-AppHub-App-Slug`)

### HTTP companion (publisher backend on `api_urls`)

- `GET bridge/user` — scoped user snapshot (requires `user.read` on token)
- `POST bridge/notify` — desktop notifications (requires `desktop.notify`)
- `POST verify-launch-token` — one-time token verification; caller IP must match `api_urls`
- App frontend calls **publisher backend proxy** — do not call Hub bridge HTTP directly from iframe

## Deploy

- **hosted:** `dist/` → zip + `manifest.json` → `POST /apps/register` (draft) → approval → store
- **iframe:** manifest with `runtime_type: iframe` + `entry_url` → register JSON or drop manifest on Hub desktop
- **local:** manifest on Hub desktop — private install, not listed in store

Portal URL for upload and testing: **`hub_portal_url`** in `apphub.publisher.json` (local file, not committed).

## i18n (en / vi) — required for UI

- All user-visible strings via i18n; always ship `locales/en.json` and `locales/vi.json`
- Sync locale with Hub when `user.profile` or bridge context provides it
- No hardcoded UI text in components (use locale keys)

## Dark / Light mode — required

- Support both themes; use semantic CSS variables / design tokens
- App must be usable in both modes inside Hub windows
- Persist preference locally when running standalone

## Code quality

- Clean, maintainable code; clear module separation (UI / logic / API)
- Prefer TypeScript; type bridge context, manifest, and API payloads
- Handle denied permissions gracefully in UI
- Never commit `.env`, `launch_token`, or secrets

## Pre-publish checklist

- [ ] `PLAN.md` updated — all completed steps marked, phases reflect current state
- [ ] `manifest.json` has correct `runtime_type`, `permissions`, `api_urls`
- [ ] Listens for `apphub:bridge:ready`; hosted: awaits `__APPHUB_STORAGE__.ready`
- [ ] Server auth via publisher backend; never trust `display_user` for authorization
- [ ] `launch_token` not exposed in client logs or UI
- [ ] Full `en` + `vi` locale files; dark + light themes usable
- [ ] Launch flow tested: `POST /apps/{slug}/launch` → app loads → bridge ready
- [ ] `apphub.publisher.json` filled locally (file is gitignored — never commit real URLs)
